{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, CV = CT.Proof.",
    "For the first part, if X exists, then ■ i X is a lower bound of{■ i x | x ∈ X}.",
    "In a T -BAO it is also the greatest: if z ≤ ■ i x for all x ∈ X, then f i (z) ≤ x for all x ∈ X, so f i (z) ≤ X and hence z ≤ ■ i X.",
    "For the second part, in a CV-BAO A the left adjoint f i of ■ i is given by the definition f i (x) = {y ∈ A | x ≤ ■ i y}.Recall from § 1 that where X is a class of BAOs, ML(X) is the set of modal logics L such that L is the logic of some subclass of X, and ALG is the class of all BAOs, we have:ML(CAV) ⊊ ML(CV) ⊊ ML(T) ⊊ ML(V) ⊊ ML(ALG).Finally, we fix our terminology for discussing homomorphisms between BAOs.",
    "Definition 5.3 (Homomorphisms)."
  ]
}